&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 7 Ward Manager- Gynaecology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you looking to lead? An exciting opportunity has arisen for a highly motivated individual to apply for the role of band 7 Ward Manager. Lillian Holland (SMH) has 12 in patient stay beds – patients are admitted for elective/emergency benign gynaecology surgery. Gynaecology Emergencies are admitted to the ward from A+E as well as the Gynaecology Emergency Room. The ward provides a separate nurse led unit for women having medical management for termination of pregnancy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a forward thinking, enthusiastic and innovative nurse who will be able to lead and motivate nursing staff in the provision of high quality patient focussed care. The successful candidate will be enthusiastic and friendly and be able to demonstrate clinical leadership skills. The successful candidate needs to be passionate about staff, patient experience and wellbeing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers huge potential for further developing your clinical, leadership and management skills in a challenging but supportive setting. The successful candidate will need to confidently manage and provide strong leadership, training and education for all staff, ensuring their involvement in the development of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a patient facing role which involves regular face to face contact with patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have a can do attitude and enjoy working on a fast paced and friendly environment then we would like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tania Berto at tania.berto@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
